   <taskbody>
      <steps class="- topic/ol task/steps ">
         <step class="- topic/li task/step ">
            <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">From the X-Author pane, click <image placement="inline"
                      width="20"
                      href="../attachments/45220109/50036849.png"
                      id="image_x3l_tw4_12c"
                      class="- topic/image "/>
               <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Check In</uicontrol>.</cmd>
            <stepresult class="- topic/itemgroup task/stepresult ">
               <p class="- topic/p ">The Check-in Options page is displayed.</p>
               <fig id="fig_dkq_ww4_12c" class="- topic/fig ">
                  <image height="400"
                         placement="break"
                         href="../attachments/45220109/50036850.png"
                         id="image_ekq_ww4_12c"
                         class="- topic/image "/>
               </fig>
            </stepresult>
         </step>
         <step class="- topic/li task/step ">
            <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Under <menucascade class="+ topic/ph ui-d/menucascade ">
                  <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Options</uicontrol>
                  <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Save</uicontrol>
               </menucascade>, choose one of three options for saving the document:</cmd>
            <info class="- topic/itemgroup task/info ">
               <p class="- topic/p ">
                  <table class="- topic/table ">
                     <tgroup cols="2" class="- topic/tgroup ">
                        <thead class="- topic/thead ">
                           <row class="- topic/row ">
                              <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                                 <p class="- topic/p ">Option</p>
                              </entry>
                              <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                                 <p class="- topic/p ">Description</p>
                              </entry>
                           </row>
                        </thead>
                        <tbody class="- topic/tbody ">
                           <row class="- topic/row ">
                              <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                                 <p class="- topic/p ">
                                    <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">With Redlines</b>
                                 </p>
                              </entry>
                              <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                                 <p class="- topic/p ">This saves a draft version of the agreement document with all
                                    markups and <i class="+ topic/ph hi-d/i ">Redlines</i> is added to the suggested file name.
                                    Selecting this option creates a Minor (Negotiator) version under
                                    the <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Document Version Details</b> related list in your
                                    Agreement record.</p>
                              </entry>
                           </row>
                           <row class="- topic/row ">
                              <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                                 <p class="- topic/p ">
                                    <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Without Redlines</b>
                                 </p>
                              </entry>
                              <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                                 <p class="- topic/p ">This saves a draft version of the document without markups and
                                    is typically done before sending an agreement to a third party
                                    for review. Track changes/redlines and comments are
                                    automatically removed from the Word file and <i class="+ topic/ph hi-d/i ">Clean</i> is
                                    added by default to the suggested file name. Selecting this
                                    option creates a Major version under the <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Document Version
                                       Details</b> related list in your Agreement record.</p>
                              </entry>
                           </row>
                           <row class="- topic/row ">
                              <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                                 <p class="- topic/p ">
                                    <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Final - to be signed</b>
                                 </p>
                              </entry>
                              <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                                 <p class="- topic/p ">This saves a version of the document without markups and also
                                    enables a PDF version of the document to be created. <i class="+ topic/ph hi-d/i ">Final
                                    </i>is added to the suggested file name. If this option is
                                    selected, both a Major Word version is saved to <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Document
                                       Version Details</b> and a PDF file is be saved to the
                                    agreement's <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Notes &amp; Attachments</b> related list.</p>
                              </entry>
                           </row>
                        </tbody>
                     </tgroup>
                  </table>
               </p>
            </info>
         </step>
         <step class="- topic/li task/step ">
            <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">In the <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Name</uicontrol> field, enter the required name for the document
               or leave it as the name suggested by X-Author. </cmd>
            <info class="- topic/itemgroup task/info ">
               <p class="- topic/p ">The default name includes the agreement name, revision number, and version type.
                  You do not need to specify a file extension in the <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Suggested
                     Name</uicontrol> field, as X-Author automatically saves it in DOCX format.</p>
            </info>
         </step>
         <step class="- topic/li task/step ">
            <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Select the required watermark option.</cmd>
            <info class="- topic/itemgroup task/info ">
               <ul class="- topic/ul ">
                  <li class="- topic/li ">Select <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Include Watermark</uicontrol>, to add one to a non-final
                     version. This option is available with the <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">With Redlines</uicontrol>
                     and <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Without Redlines</uicontrol> options.</li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Include Watermark </uicontrol>is automatically deselected (greyed out) if you are saving the document as <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Final - to be signed</uicontrol>.<note type="note" class="- topic/note ">
                        <p class="- topic/p ">If the document already contains a watermark, the watermark will be removed instead when this option is chosen.</p>
                     </note>
                  </li>
               </ul>
            </info>
         </step>
         <step class="- topic/li task/step ">
            <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Select <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Reconcile Document</uicontrol> to synchronize the Salesforce
               Agreement object fields with those that were updated in the document. </cmd>
            <info class="- topic/itemgroup task/info ">
               <p class="- topic/p ">See<xref href="../reconciliation_45220099_45220099/45220099.dita"
                        format="dita"
                        class="- topic/xref ">Reconciliation</xref> for more details.</p>
            </info>
         </step>
         <step class="- topic/li task/step ">
            <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Select <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Mark as private</uicontrol> to enable the <i class="+ topic/ph hi-d/i ">Private</i> indicator for this agreement (only for use in custom implementationsâ€“see the Apttus Contract Management Administrator Guide for more information). </cmd>
         </step>
         <step class="- topic/li task/step ">
            <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Click <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Submit</uicontrol> to confirm check-in of the document. </cmd>
            <stepresult class="- topic/itemgroup task/stepresult ">
               <p class="- topic/p ">The document is checked in to Salesforce and the <i class="+ topic/ph hi-d/i ">new document version is
                     downloaded</i> from the agreement record. </p>
            </stepresult>
         </step>
         <step class="- topic/li task/step ">
            <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Close the document you just checked in (no need to save) and load the newly downloaded document to continue working with the agreement, if necessary.</cmd>
         </step>
      </steps>
      <postreq class="- topic/section task/postreq ">
         <note type="note" class="- topic/note ">
            <p class="- topic/p ">If there are any invalid fields in your agreement, a message is displayed and the check-in is not completed. Return to <xref href="../working_with_fields_45220_45220124/45220124.dita"
                     format="dita"
                     class="- topic/xref ">Document &gt; Fields</xref> to validate fields and make corrected as needed.</p>
         </note>
      </postreq>
